The '''Nuremberg International Human Rights Award''' is a German award founded on September 17, 1995. The date chosen is significant; 60 years earlier, the [[Nuremberg Race Laws]] were adopted. Also, on September 17, 1939, [[Soviet invasion of Poland|Poland was invaded]] by the [[Soviet Union]], soon after the [[invasion of Poland|German invasion]] that marked the beginning of World War II

The winner is endowed with 15,000 euros (20,235 USD).

